# Naming Conventions (Dart/Flutter)

## Files

- `snake_case.dart`
- Test files: `{name}_test.dart` colocated.
- One public class per file (private helpers OK).

## Identifiers

- Classes / typedefs / enums: `UpperCamelCase`
- Variables / parameters / methods: `lowerCamelCase`
- Private: `_underscorePrefix`
- Constants: `lowerCamelCase` for class statics; `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE` for top-level rare.

## Patterns

- Booleans answer yes/no: `isLoading`, `hasError`, `canJoin`.
- Units in measurable names: `expiryInSeconds`, `widthPx`, `priceCents`.
- Collections plural: `games`, `courts`.
- Drop noise: NOT `gameData`, `gameInfo`, `gameManager`. Just `game` / `games` / `gameRepository`.

## Flutter idioms

- Widgets named for what they render: `CourtMarker`, `FillBar`, `GameRow`. NOT `CourtMarkerWidget`.
- Notifier suffix on Riverpod notifiers: `GamesNotifier`, `AuthNotifier`.
- Provider suffix on Riverpod providers: `gameRepositoryProvider` (generated by codegen).
- Repository interface = noun + "Repository": `GameRepository`. Concrete = `SupabaseGameRepository`.

## Anti-patterns

- `AbstractFactoryManagerHelperServiceImpl` — at most ONE of these words.
- `getData()` — what data?
- `utils.dart` — split by responsibility.


